  1. Terminators send the Batch to SQL Server using mssql NPM package
       GO        Test then process the Batch via mssql.Request().query()
       RUN       Test then process the Batch via mssql.Request().batch()
       TEST      DB Engine query parse (SET NOEXEC ON) then resume the Batch
  2. Admistrative Commands  that mostly* do not affect the active Batch
  HELP EXIT WHO VANTAGE REPL LOGLEVEL CONFIG REMOVE SERVER LIST CACHE BCP SQLCMD SQLOG
       HELP      Shows usage overview for CLI commands (or try 'LIST -v')
       HELP [command] -or- [command] --HELP  for [command] usage
       * SQLCMD processes the Batch much like GO or RUN, EXIT abandons the Batch,
         CACHE owns the Batch. ('CACHE' aka '?' to list or '? -b clear')
  3. Injectors overload the Batch with a previous query, script or Batch
       ARCHIVE   Batches processed in previous sessions from file
       HISTORY   Batches processed during current session from buffer
       QUERY     Query template strings from queries javascript object
       SCRIPT    Files previously stored in the ./scripts subfolder
